headline: Bitcoin hashrate at record, margins pinched: Will miners sell or pivot amid AI power land‑grab?
summary: Bitcoin network difficulty reached 136.04 trillion on Sept. 4, while dollar hashprice slipped to about $52 per petahash per day this week. Per Hashrate Index, the last adjustment set a new high for difficulty, and the forward market now prices an average hashprice near $49.17 per PH per day for the next six months.
